title: For Sale:  Nickel Fitz Colt Police Positive
postcontent:
Early Fritz  style Nickel plated Colt  Police Positive Special 38 S# 69XXX (1917) with early Rampant Colt superimposed over the stylized "C", grooved hammer top, barrel cut to 2 1/8” possibly made by J. Henry Fitzgerald himself and not in the Colt factory. The craftsmanship on this is outstanding it’s well within the time frame and has the patina and the grooved hammer and the barrel has been correctly crowned. The timing and lock up is good and the bore and rifling are in good condition along with the cylinder chambers. The grips are quality reproductions and it comes with a nice high hip holster.
 
 I believe it was made by J. Fitzgerald himself during his career as a New York Cop and competition shooter. No self appointed expert can verify it either because no records were kept when he made them for clients, just the ones made by Colt. Also for you safety experts there are no documented accidental discharges because of the front trigger guard being removed.
 
 Fitzgerald built many of his specials for clients many of these were law enforcement officers and soldiers during WWI and WWII. This pistol has J F stamped on right and 1 s on the left bottom of the grip frame, possibly J Henry Fitzgerald only the Shadow knows for sure. This 99 year old Colt is well within the time frame and has the patina and possibly customized by Fitzgerald and not Colt Factory made. $525 or trade call Bill REDACTED
